    <p>Anybody have any ideas? During Seal missions, David Cooper sought opportunities to spotlight the need for his men to speak up, especially with newer team members. He was not subtle. â€œFor example, when youâ€™re in an urban environment, windows are bad,â€ he tells me. â€œYou stand in front of one, and you can get shot by a sniper and never know where it came from. So if youâ€™re a new guy and you see me standing in front of a window in Fallujah, what are you going to say? Are you going to tell me to move my ass, or are you going to stand there quietly and let me get shot? When I ask new guys that question, they say, â€˜Iâ€™ll tell you to move.â€™ So I tell them, â€˜Well, thatâ€™s exactly how you should conduct yourself all the time around here, with every single decision.â€™ â€
